    <text id="F8530T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Edward McPherson, in writing to his father, expresses his intention to visit a
                    Mrs. Carson and mentions seeing other friends. McPherson also comments on the
                    state of the stock market. </p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
              

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1857-09-06"><abbr expan="September">Sept.</abbr> 6.</date>
                        <name type="place">
                            <abbr expan="Philadelphia">Phila.</abbr>
                        </name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My dear Father --</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I reached <abbr expan="Philadelphia">Phila.</abbr> at 10 last night-- too late to
                    call upon Mrs. Carson who, I understand, was expected here yesterday. With a
                    view to surprise her &amp; escort her on her way home, I made every effort
                    to get off from <abbr expan="New York">N.Y.</abbr> in the 2 o'clock boat, as I
                    supposed she could take that train. I was 15 minutes too late &amp; was
                    compelled to wait until 6 in the <abbr expan="evening">eveg.</abbr>-- I intended
                    getting up in the morning to meet her at the depot, but being more than usually
                    tired, overslept myself.--Please tell Mr. Carson of my efforts.</p>

                <p>I saw <abbr expan="Henry">Hen.</abbr> Duehler &amp; Mr.
                    <unclear>Nead</unclear> when I arrived, &amp; <abbr expan="received"
                    >recd.</abbr> Mother's letter by the former. This morning, I <pb n="2"/>
                    <abbr expan="received">recd.</abbr> yours enclosing two others.--</p>

                <p><unclear>Jos.</unclear>
                    <unclear>Mchaffey</unclear> &amp; <abbr expan="William">Wm.</abbr> M.'s wife
                    are at the St. Lawrence. They came yesterday, &amp; will go home tomorrow.
                    They report all well at Marietta.</p>

                <p><abbr expan="Andrew">And<hi rend="super">w</hi>.</abbr> has been very much <del
                        hand="h1"/> tired the last few weeks, but looks well. <abbr expan="New York"
                        >N.Y.</abbr> is crowded to overflowing, &amp; our Hotels are filling up.</p>

                <p>I have nothing new to write, &amp; must be brief, as there is an accumulation
                    of business to <del hand="h1">atte</del> transact.</p>

                <p>Love <hi rend="underline">to Mother</hi>,</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <abbr expan="Edward">Edwd</abbr>
                    </signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Money is very tight here today. The market will be
                        unsettled for some time.</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
